{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos592.erdos_592 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos592.erdos_592.","id":"vf_a4533cf5a1c3d112","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #592: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Determine which countable ordinals $\\beta$ have the property that, if $\\alpha=\\omega^{^\\beta}$, then in any red/blue colouring of the edges of $K_\\alpha$ there is either a red $K_\\alpha$ or a blue $K_3$. Current best: This property holds for $\\beta=2$ and not for $3\\leq \\beta <\\omega$ (Specker \\cite{Sp57}) and for $\\beta=\\omega$ (Chang \\cite{Ch72}). Galvin and Larson \\cite{GaLa74} have shown that if $\\beta\\geq 3$ has this property then $\\beta$ must be 'additively indecomposable', so that in particular $\\beta=\\omega^\\gamma$ for some $\\gamma<\\omega_1$. Galvin and Larson conjecture that every $\\beta\\geq 3$ of this form has this property. Prize: $1000. Tags: ramsey theory, set theory.","id":"vf_bf6ae0270fe30646","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/592.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_a4533cf5a1c3d112","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:592","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_a4533cf5a1c3d112","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_bf6ae0270fe30646","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_